WEBVTT

00:34.160 --> 00:35.787
<i>Rule #1:</i>

00:36.788 --> 00:39.791
<i>Make sure you know everything
about those you visit.</i>

00:41.000 --> 00:44.504
<i>2: Never spend more than 10 minutes.</i>

00:44.671 --> 00:47.924
<i>Every extra minute increases the chance
of someone returning home unexpectedly.</i>

00:51.344 --> 00:53.555
<i>3: Do not leave any DNA traces.</i>

00:59.310 --> 01:03.064
<i>4: Don't waste time getting
an expensive reproduction.</i>

01:03.231 --> 01:06.985
<i>Even a simple forgery will
go unnoticed for weeks.</i>

01:09.571 --> 01:14.117
<i>5: Sooner or later,
one of two things will happen.</i>

01:14.284 --> 01:19.038
<i>You find a work of art so valuable
that you never need to worry again...</i>

01:19.205 --> 01:20.498
<i>or...</i>

01:20.665 --> 01:21.958
<i>you'll get caught.</i>

01:22.125 --> 01:25.295
HEADHUNTERS

01:48.651 --> 01:50.570
<i>My name is Roger Brown.</i>

01:50.737 --> 01:52.489
<i>I'm 5'6" tall.</i>

01:52.655 --> 01:55.909
<i>You don't need a Ph.D to realize
that I overcompensate for my height.</i>

01:58.411 --> 02:02.123
<i>For instance,
my house is worth 30 million kroner.</i>

02:02.290 --> 02:04.834
<i>I don't like it
and I can't afford it. But she...</i>

02:05.001 --> 02:06.377
Of course you have to come!

02:06.544 --> 02:07.921
<i>She loved it.</i>

02:08.086 --> 02:10.840
How often does one
of your girlfriends open a gallery?

02:11.007 --> 02:14.010
<i>I told her
I had inherited the money.</i>

02:14.177 --> 02:16.554
<i>I had to give her
some kind of explanation.</i>

02:16.721 --> 02:18.431
<i>But all I've inherited is bad genes.</i>

02:18.598 --> 02:22.352
We've gone through a long and intricate
process to reach the truth in this case.

02:22.519 --> 02:25.897
<i>For someone like me to get
what he wants, only one thing matters...</i>

02:26.064 --> 02:27.565
<i>Money.</i>

02:27.732 --> 02:28.775
Go ahead, open it.

02:28.942 --> 02:30.568
<i>Lots of money.</i>

02:37.867 --> 02:41.079
<i>But there is one thing
Diana wants more than anything else.</i>

02:42.664 --> 02:45.208
<i>And that is exactly the one thing
I do not want to give her.</i>

02:48.753 --> 02:51.381
- Isn't she cute?
- Real cute.

02:55.885 --> 02:59.097
<i>You see, Diana StrÃ¸m-Eliassen is
one of those tall, smart beauties.</i>

02:59.264 --> 03:00.682
Hi, guys! The large paintings go
to the back, okay?

03:00.849 --> 03:05.228
<i>The type used to being loved.
The type who take love for granted.</i>

03:06.229 --> 03:08.648
<i>And there are plenty of men
who would love her.</i>

03:08.815 --> 03:10.692
<i>Men taller than 5'6".</i>

03:15.822 --> 03:17.699
<i>But soon my time will come.</i>

03:17.866 --> 03:21.411
<i>My opportunity. I can feel it.</i>

03:21.578 --> 03:22.996
<i>In the meantime,
I play for high stakes.</i>

03:23.162 --> 03:26.207
<i>If you don't gamble, you don't win.</i>

03:31.254 --> 03:33.131
What are your plans for tomorrow?

03:33.298 --> 03:35.675
- Why?
- We have a dinner invitation.

03:37.719 --> 03:39.262
We're invited to dinner.

03:40.972 --> 03:42.181
We are invited to dinner?

03:42.348 --> 03:44.058
Yes. There's someone
I want you to meet.

03:44.225 --> 03:46.185
Are you telling others about us, Lotte?

03:46.352 --> 03:48.187
There's just someone
I'd like you to meet.

03:48.354 --> 03:52.233
This ends right here and now.
I'm really sorry about it.

03:52.400 --> 03:55.528
- Please don't.
- No no no, Lotte!

03:56.696 --> 03:59.657
- You and me do not exist.
- Please stop it.

04:10.710 --> 04:12.503
An impressive resumÃ©
you've got here, Lander.

04:12.670 --> 04:16.466
Thank you. Yes, I believe
I'm the right man for Pathfinder.

04:18.384 --> 04:20.386
I would like to hear a bit about
your life outside the job as well.

04:20.553 --> 04:22.055
Is there such a thing?

04:24.557 --> 04:28.478
So you live here in Oslo?
And are married to? Thank you, Oda.

04:28.645 --> 04:31.105
Camilla.
We've been married for nine years.

04:31.272 --> 04:33.191
- Two kids. They are in school.
- Does she hold a job?

04:33.358 --> 04:35.318
Yes. At a downtown law firm.

04:35.485 --> 04:38.655
Nine-to-five, every day?
Who stays home if the children fall ill?

04:38.821 --> 04:40.114
She does, of course.

04:40.281 --> 04:42.283
So there's no maid
at home during the day?

04:42.450 --> 04:43.451
- No.
- Dog?

04:43.618 --> 04:45.787
- Do we have a dog? No.
- No? Allergic?

04:45.954 --> 04:47.246
No.

04:59.509 --> 05:02.303
How much would you consider that your
reputation as a leader is worth, Lander?

05:02.470 --> 05:05.390
My... reputation?
What do you mean?

05:06.849 --> 05:08.810
This work is by Julian Opie

05:08.977 --> 05:10.269
and is worth a quarter of a million.

05:10.436 --> 05:11.896
Do you own any art
in the same price range?

05:12.063 --> 05:13.606
Actually, yes.

05:13.773 --> 05:17.026
A Munch lithograph.
"The Brooch."

05:17.193 --> 05:19.278
Could you estimate
its value just by looking at it?

05:19.445 --> 05:21.280
- Well, I'm not sure.
- You're not sure.

05:21.447 --> 05:24.033
This one, for instance,
consists of a few circles and lines.

05:24.200 --> 05:25.827
The coloration is monotone
and without texture.

05:25.994 --> 05:28.663
The only thing--
I repeat, the only thing--

05:28.830 --> 05:30.915
that makes this work worth
a quarter of a million

05:31.082 --> 05:32.583
is the artist's reputation.

05:32.750 --> 05:34.794
And your point is
the same thing goes for leaders?

05:34.961 --> 05:36.504
Exactly.

05:38.923 --> 05:41.426
Which is why
you will not take this job.

05:43.344 --> 05:46.848
- What?
- My God. You applied for it yourself.

05:51.602 --> 05:53.354
What else was I supposed to do?

05:53.521 --> 05:56.149
You should have had
someone tip us off to you

05:56.315 --> 05:58.192
and then pretended you didn't know
about it when we got in touch.

05:58.359 --> 05:59.736
But...

05:59.902 --> 06:01.988
It's all a game, Lander.

06:03.239 --> 06:06.200
Listen. Pathfinder's chairman
and finance manager

06:06.367 --> 06:08.411
will be here tomorrow,
and I'd like you to meet them.

06:08.578 --> 06:10.705
You're going to listen politely to them,

06:10.872 --> 06:13.541
then you will explain
why you are no longer interested

06:13.708 --> 06:17.003
- and wish them good luck.
- But I would not seem serious.

06:17.170 --> 06:19.881
No. They will see you as ambitious,

06:20.048 --> 06:22.008
as someone who knows his own worth.

06:24.385 --> 06:26.012
Lander...

06:27.972 --> 06:30.058
- This is your opportunity.
- Opportunity?

06:30.224 --> 06:32.810
Let me build your reputation

06:34.520 --> 06:37.732
and I promise you a position which
quintuples your income within two years.

06:37.899 --> 06:39.776
- Within two years?
- Within two years.

06:39.942 --> 06:41.819
How can you promise this?

06:41.986 --> 06:46.032
Because I have never given a client
a recommendation he hasn't followed.

06:46.199 --> 06:48.951
- Never?
- Never.

06:49.118 --> 06:50.953
But how?

06:51.120 --> 06:52.997
The answer starts with an "R."

06:53.164 --> 06:57.460
- Reputation?
- My entire career is based on it.

07:00.046 --> 07:01.506
Hi.

07:03.549 --> 07:05.468
- Yes?
- I set you up for the interview

07:05.635 --> 07:08.096
with Jeremias Lander and Pathfinder
tomorrow at 12 o'clock.

07:09.097 --> 07:11.641
- The information is in the file.
- Great.

07:11.808 --> 07:13.476
But listen,

07:13.643 --> 07:17.563
your wife is opening her gallery
this weekend, and I wondered...

07:17.730 --> 07:19.857
could I attend?

07:20.024 --> 07:22.485
- Are you invited?
- Exactly my question!

07:22.652 --> 07:25.154
- Am I?
- Are you?

07:25.321 --> 07:28.449
<i>I got an invoice of 357,000</i>

07:28.616 --> 07:30.576
<i>for redecoration
in Kasper Hansen Street.</i>

07:30.743 --> 07:32.912
- Yes, that's correct.
- <i>Well, what's that about?</i>

07:33.079 --> 07:36.916
I helped Diana with some expenses.
She opens her own gallery on Friday.

07:37.083 --> 07:40.294
<i>You have to start cutting down
on your expenses, Roger.</i>

07:40.461 --> 07:42.463
<i>You may go bankrupt at any time.</i>

07:42.630 --> 07:44.340
I'm working on it, Frode.
I'm working on it.

07:44.507 --> 07:46.592
<i>As your accountant,
it's my duty to inform you</i>

07:46.759 --> 07:48.553
<i>about the seriousness
of the situation.</i>

07:48.719 --> 07:52.473
<i>You have overdrawn your account by
several hundred thousands for dinners...</i>

07:52.640 --> 07:55.268
There's a call coming in here.
I'll call you later.

07:56.519 --> 07:59.772
We have a candidate.
Jeremias Lander, lives at SkÃ¸yen.

08:03.943 --> 08:06.612
Okay. Got him. When?

08:06.779 --> 08:09.157
He has a meeting at Alfa tomorrow at 12.
It will last one hour.

08:09.323 --> 08:12.368
- <i>Nobody home?</i>
- No dog, no maid, wife works downtown.

08:12.535 --> 08:14.245
See you in 20 minutes.

09:44.794 --> 09:46.837
<i>The fence in Gothenburg demanded 50%.</i>

09:48.089 --> 09:50.883
<i>Ove Kjikerud charged 20%
to disconnect alarms,</i>

09:51.050 --> 09:53.511
<i>fetch the art in my garage,
and bring it to Sweden by car.</i>

09:53.678 --> 09:58.099
<i>To get him employed at Tripolis was
one of my smartest moves.</i>

09:58.266 --> 10:00.476
<i>I myself was left with 80,000.</i>

10:00.643 --> 10:02.353
<i>80,000.</i>

10:02.520 --> 10:05.398
<i>Not even enough for my next
quarterly payment on my house.</i>

10:06.899 --> 10:08.526
<i>Something had to be done.</i>

10:13.823 --> 10:15.533
- Nice to see you.
- Hi.

10:15.700 --> 10:18.035
- Hi.
- Thanks for coming.

10:29.839 --> 10:31.632
It's looking real good.

10:31.799 --> 10:34.010
Not even half of the guests
have arrived yet.

10:34.176 --> 10:36.554
But I don't have the time
to greet anyone either because...

10:36.721 --> 10:39.265
Listen, it's going just fine.

10:39.432 --> 10:42.768
- Congratulations. Fantastic exhibition.
- Thank you.

10:42.935 --> 10:45.271
- Something crazy happened today.
- Like what?

10:45.438 --> 10:48.149
I cannot tell you now,
but I want you to meet him.

10:48.316 --> 10:49.650
Meet who?

11:07.918 --> 11:09.879
So this is my husband, Roger Brown.

11:10.046 --> 11:11.464
- Clas Greve.
- Nice to meet you.

11:11.630 --> 11:14.008
Clas just moved here
from the Netherlands.

11:14.175 --> 11:17.178
Excuse me.
Hi, are you on your way?

11:18.220 --> 11:21.682
No, a few screaming kids
just liven up the party...

11:24.769 --> 11:26.479
So what brings you to Norway? Work?

11:26.645 --> 11:28.773
No. I inherited
my grandmother's apartment.

11:28.939 --> 11:30.566
- She was Norwegian?
- Yes.

11:30.733 --> 11:34.528
And a few months ago,
I chose to go into early retirement.

11:34.695 --> 11:36.155
So now I've moved here

11:36.322 --> 11:37.865
- to redecorate the apartment.
- So you retired?

11:38.032 --> 11:39.283
- Yes.
- From what?

11:39.450 --> 11:42.620
I was the CEO
of a Dutch technology company.

11:42.787 --> 11:46.624
I work with GPS sales.

11:46.791 --> 11:49.251
Dutch? Not HOTE, by any chance?

11:49.418 --> 11:50.711
Yes, exactly.

11:50.878 --> 11:55.007
Weren't they just bought up
by a large American company? Amtech?

11:56.717 --> 11:58.761
- You are also in the business?
- No.

12:00.721 --> 12:02.014
But why did you quit?
Isn't it exciting?

12:02.181 --> 12:03.724
I won't bore you with job chatter.

12:03.891 --> 12:07.645
I'm in the recruitment business.
You won't bore me with job chatter.

12:09.397 --> 12:11.399
Are you familiar with Pathfinder?

12:11.565 --> 12:14.860
Yes, of course.
They were our competitors.

12:15.861 --> 12:19.448
Roger, I'm sorry, I have to go.
But enjoy the rest of your evening.

12:19.615 --> 12:23.452
Clas! Pathfinder seeks a new manager.

12:23.619 --> 12:26.789
Someone who can stand up
against foreign takeovers.

12:26.956 --> 12:28.791
- How about a meeting?
- Sorry, Roger.

12:28.958 --> 12:31.877
Then let's have lunch.
Monday at 12:00.

12:32.044 --> 12:34.880
We could drop the job chatter
and talk about other things...

12:35.047 --> 12:37.591
art, redecoration,
Polish handymen.

12:37.758 --> 12:40.469
Could I have a pen?
I'll write down the restaurant's name.

12:40.636 --> 12:41.971
You're not used to being turned down?

12:45.474 --> 12:48.644
A farewell present
for long and faithful service?

12:48.811 --> 12:50.896
No, I stole it.

12:54.358 --> 12:57.695
See you then.
Give my regards to your charming wife.

12:57.862 --> 12:59.447
I will.

13:09.915 --> 13:14.128
- This is my husband.
- Roger Brown. Nice to meet you.

13:14.295 --> 13:17.506
- Brede Sperre, Kripos.
- Yes, we've seen you on TV.

13:17.673 --> 13:19.758
He investigates
art burglaries now.

13:19.925 --> 13:21.469
I thought you investigated murders.

13:21.635 --> 13:24.305
Yes, but this is getting so big
that we sent in all our resources.

13:24.472 --> 13:27.641
We're going to stop this now.
Are you in the art business as well?

13:27.808 --> 13:32.104
No, I work as a headhunter.
In the recruitment business, for Alfa.

13:32.271 --> 13:34.398
I see. One of the partners.

13:34.565 --> 13:35.608
What do you mean?

13:35.774 --> 13:39.403
Well, I complimented your wife here
on her expensive earrings.

13:39.570 --> 13:41.322
She said they were
a present from you.

13:41.489 --> 13:43.115
Yes.

13:44.325 --> 13:46.660
The best of us
get good bonus deals.

13:49.997 --> 13:53.626
I wish we had those
in my line of work as well.

13:53.792 --> 13:55.127
- Sperre?
- Yes?

13:55.294 --> 13:57.296
We're from VG.
Could we have a photo?

13:57.463 --> 13:59.173
Of course.

14:03.969 --> 14:06.889
Hi. How nice of you to come.

14:19.568 --> 14:21.612
Roger? Are you coming?

14:26.700 --> 14:28.369
Look at this.

14:28.536 --> 14:31.539
"The Calydonian Boar Hunt,"
by Rubens.

14:31.705 --> 14:36.210
It was stolen when the Germans looted
the gallery in Antwerp in 1941.

14:36.377 --> 14:40.089
It's been missing ever since.
Do you know where it is now?

14:40.256 --> 14:41.298
No.

14:41.465 --> 14:44.260
In Clas Grave's apartment
in Oscar Street.

14:45.886 --> 14:47.763
- What?
- Clas Grave's grandmother had

14:47.930 --> 14:51.183
a secret love affair
with a German officer during the war.

14:51.350 --> 14:54.436
But he was arrested
and shot a few days later.

14:54.603 --> 14:57.231
She panicked, fearing someone
would discover the relationship.

14:57.398 --> 14:59.358
And then she hid the painting?

14:59.525 --> 15:02.528
- Yes, something of the sort.
- Oh well, but it's not genuine.

15:02.695 --> 15:06.031
I don't think German officers
collected reproductions, Roger.

15:07.700 --> 15:09.118
Well, why did he tell you about it?

15:09.285 --> 15:12.288
He came by the gallery
to ask if I could evaluate it

15:12.454 --> 15:14.206
or if I knew someone who could.

15:16.625 --> 15:19.503
You're saying that
Clas Greve has a genuine Rubens

15:19.670 --> 15:20.963
hanging in his apartment
in Oscar Street?

15:21.130 --> 15:22.131
- Yes.
- Here in Oslo?

15:22.298 --> 15:27.052
Yes. But I offered
to contact an art museum

15:27.219 --> 15:30.222
to have it moved as soon as possible.
Next week.

15:30.389 --> 15:34.226
You don't place a painting
like this in a safe-deposit box.

15:35.978 --> 15:37.396
How much do you think it's worth?

15:38.564 --> 15:42.234
Tens of millions.
Maybe a hundred.

15:49.241 --> 15:53.454
Do you know what I think?
I think we should celebrate.

15:53.621 --> 15:56.665
Celebrate what?

15:56.832 --> 16:01.378
That you opened your own gallery.

16:03.213 --> 16:04.798
And the two of us.

16:04.965 --> 16:07.301
Thanks for supporting me, Roger.

16:07.468 --> 16:10.095
Everything is going to be fine.

16:10.262 --> 16:12.222
What do you mean?

16:13.307 --> 16:17.227
That you and I should
start thinking about the future.

16:31.241 --> 16:33.869
- Ove here.
- <i>We have a candidate.</i>

16:34.036 --> 16:35.329
Do you know what the time is?

16:35.496 --> 16:38.916
<i>His name is Clas Greve.
He lives in 25 Oscar Street.</i>

16:39.083 --> 16:40.834
What, he is grave?

16:41.001 --> 16:42.753
No, his name is Greve.

16:45.214 --> 16:46.382
Ove?

16:49.968 --> 16:51.428
Ove, what's happening? Ove?

16:51.595 --> 16:53.931
Sorry. Natasha is here.

16:54.098 --> 16:55.641
Come again?

16:55.808 --> 16:57.267
<i>Meet me at the cabin tomorrow.</i>

16:57.434 --> 16:59.687
No, not tomorrow! It's Saturday.

16:59.853 --> 17:01.563
I've got her for the whole weekend.

17:01.730 --> 17:03.399
We want to do something nice.
Not tomorrow.

17:03.565 --> 17:06.318
This is a big deal, Ove.
We only have a couple of days.

17:09.570 --> 17:12.324
- <i>One o'clock!</i>
- Yes, okay.

17:25.045 --> 17:28.006
- You are so sweet.
- Good morning.

17:34.179 --> 17:36.348
- Listen.
- Yes?

17:37.474 --> 17:39.143
What you said yesterday
about the future.

17:40.310 --> 17:41.854
- Yes?
- Does it include the sound

17:42.020 --> 17:45.482
of tiny feet
shuffling along these corridors?

17:46.483 --> 17:49.820
- Maybe.
- Don't give me "maybe," Roger.

17:52.990 --> 17:55.033
I told you yesterday
that everything will be fine,

17:55.200 --> 17:57.745
- and it will.
- But I want that conversation now.

17:57.911 --> 18:00.122
Definitely, but I have
an important meeting first.

18:01.749 --> 18:03.917
- Do you think I'm stupid?
- Hmm?

18:04.084 --> 18:06.795
- You have an important meeting?
- Yes.

18:07.838 --> 18:10.090
A meeting that was
set up during the night?

18:10.257 --> 18:13.051
I have to go.
I'll call you later.

18:16.555 --> 18:19.057
- What are you so scared of?
- Nothing.

18:19.224 --> 18:21.435
I'm scared of dogs
and you when you are like this.

18:21.602 --> 18:22.644
Don't just make jokes about it.

18:22.811 --> 18:24.730
If you want us to be childless
the rest of our lives,

18:24.897 --> 18:26.064
I would really like to know.

18:26.231 --> 18:28.025
Didn't you hear me?
We'll have the conversation,

18:28.192 --> 18:29.943
but not now because I have
an important meeting.

18:30.110 --> 18:32.279
I've tried to talk about this
for seven years, Roger.

18:32.446 --> 18:35.574
And it will take another seven years
if you keep nagging this way.

18:38.952 --> 18:40.829
I didn't mean that.

18:42.414 --> 18:44.541
You will never give me a child.

19:03.060 --> 19:06.313
So... how many millions
are we talking about?

19:08.148 --> 19:09.274
Maybe up to a hundred.

19:09.441 --> 19:11.610
A hundred?

19:14.655 --> 19:17.032
- This happens every time, Ove.
- Eh?

19:17.199 --> 19:18.659
I've told you I don't like
those things lying around.

19:18.826 --> 19:22.329
Don't start again.
You know I always carry weapons.

19:22.496 --> 19:24.957
At home, I've got weapons everywhere.

19:25.123 --> 19:27.626
Got a gun within reach in every room.

19:28.669 --> 19:32.422
You should get one as well.
Sooner or later they'll be coming.

19:32.589 --> 19:34.258
We do it this way:

19:34.424 --> 19:36.885
You go to Gothenburg
and get a reproduction.

19:37.052 --> 19:39.054
There are many available,
but we need a good one.

19:39.221 --> 19:41.390
I have lunch with Clas Greve on Monday.
Then I will get...

19:41.557 --> 19:42.891
Ove?

19:56.113 --> 19:57.489
Women.

19:58.991 --> 20:02.786
Like I tried to say before I was
interrupted by a Russian prostitute,

20:04.204 --> 20:06.248
I have lunch with Greve on Monday.

20:06.415 --> 20:08.083
I'll find out then
when the apartment is empty,

20:08.250 --> 20:10.294
so that I can fetch the painting.

20:10.460 --> 20:13.005
You go to Sweden immediately. Now.

20:13.171 --> 20:16.133
Okay. No, shit, I can't.

20:16.300 --> 20:18.385
- What?
- I'm busy.

20:18.552 --> 20:20.053
