in this situation before.

22:38.066 --> 22:41.486
- You practically dribbled over me on...
- Dribbled?

22:41.653 --> 22:45.240
You drooled when we met at the gallery,
and with good reason.

22:45.407 --> 22:48.160
On that occasion, the problem
was not that I was a foreigner,

22:48.326 --> 22:50.203
but that I was not interested in a job.

22:50.370 --> 22:52.956
But you get to reflect a lot
during a weekend, and I concluded

22:53.123 --> 22:56.168
that redecoration is not
that interesting in the long run.

22:56.334 --> 23:00.505
So if it's okay with you,
why don't we simply drop the charade?

23:05.302 --> 23:06.803
I surrender.

23:08.889 --> 23:11.183
But I still need more data on you.

23:11.349 --> 23:13.518
- For my client.
- Do you play squash?

23:24.279 --> 23:25.280
Are you married?

23:25.447 --> 23:27.240
- Divorced.
- Children?

23:27.407 --> 23:28.950
- Unfortunately not.
- Dog?

23:29.117 --> 23:30.660
Yes.

23:30.827 --> 23:33.705
I've got one.
He is in Amsterdam.

23:33.872 --> 23:36.333
- In quarantine?
- I'll fly down to get him tomorrow.

23:44.758 --> 23:47.344
The GPS business is a tough one?

23:47.511 --> 23:49.805
- Your back.
- Oh.

23:49.971 --> 23:53.350
- That's from the army.
- The army?

23:53.517 --> 23:55.894
I enrolled when I was 18.

23:56.978 --> 24:00.565
After a few years I was enlisted
in an elite unit which specialized...

24:00.732 --> 24:03.568
- Specialized in what?
- Tracking.

24:03.735 --> 24:06.988
- Tracking of?
- People.

24:07.155 --> 24:08.782
Missing people, fugitives.

24:09.783 --> 24:11.368
And the technology came from HOTE?

24:11.535 --> 24:13.411
Exactly.

24:13.578 --> 24:16.581
They produced
microscopic transmitters.

24:16.748 --> 24:21.461
I had some ideas for improvements,
so they recruited me.

24:23.130 --> 24:24.840
Where did you get those scars?

24:25.006 --> 24:26.550
